# PART 1: BRAND POSITIONING

---

## Exercise 01 — Brand Journey Framework

### 📝 Your Answers

**Desired Outcome:**
1. Create worlds that shimmer and shine — books, hymns, art, technologies not yet invented — that are still read, sung, and gathered around 100, 300, 500 years from now
2. Become one of the greatest fantasy authors of all time. Earn the right for E.I. Werner to be named in the same breath as J.R.R. Tolkien and J.K. Rowling
3. Build a living mythology — ONCE — rooted in timeless human truth, that expresses itself through every medium the world offers
4. Take the people brave enough to get on early all the way there. The first believers are part of the story permanently
5. Inspire others to declare their own ambitions — create a virtuous cycle where their courage fuels yours and yours fuels theirs
6. Financially sustain the creative life through the work itself
7. Write books that stir and inspire leaders across art, business, politics, and philosophy — work that crosses the walls of genre because the truth in it is universal

**Reputation Requirement:**
> I'm a young writer worth betting on. My perspective is studied and unique. My commitment is absolute and unfettered. My ambition is boundless and unapologetic.

**Required Actions:**
- Write consistently
- Stream live writing sessions consistently (the archive becomes proof)
- Ship writing projects people can actually read and engage with
- Maintain quality over quantity in all content decisions
- Invest in thoughtful art direction — cover design, merch, visual identity
- Share the creative process openly, including how you use AI
- Be genuinely present and accessible for paying members first
- Maintain a degree of authorial distance publicly — presence without overexposure

**Learning Gaps:**
- Video editing
- Social media strategy
- Digital community engagement

