## Exercise 04 — Brand Prison Test

### 📝 Your Answers

**Dread Topic (what to avoid):**
> Being locked into WoW or any single game as the identity. Gaming is part of who I am — not the point of the brand. Don't want to be known as a specific game streamer. Variety gaming only.

**Viral Handcuff Check:**
> No handcuffs yet. Clean slate — advantage of being early.

**Core Subjects (meeting all three criteria):**
1. The craft of writing
2. Comparative mythology and fantasy worldbuilding
3. People who go all in on a creative life — writers, artists, high performers, gamers who burn with intention

**Human Layer Inventory:**
1. Spends winters in Costa Rica — surfs, goes barefoot, a New Yorker who became a real surfer
2. One of four brothers — grew up in a full house
3. Loves late night drinks and long conversations
4. Excellent dancer — better than he has any right to be
5. Worked for Kanye West (Yeezy) and Kim Kardashian (Skims) — informs taste, fashion, and how he thinks about personal brand
6. Founded the Gentleman's Literary Forum — a book club with Vanderbilt fraternity brothers, 33 books deep and still going
7. Loves World of Warcraft — genuinely, not performatively
8. A loner who spends most of his time alone
9. Can move through different social worlds but the cool kid life feels like cosplay — knows where home is
10. The Outside Inn Discord — 10 friends, some since age 5, built through gaming
11. Large and growing beard
12. Grew up modern Orthodox Jewish — still part of his family's world

**Prison Test Response:**
> "If my brand stayed exactly the same for the next 5 years and it was working — the writing continuing, the community growing slowly and steadily — I would feel happy and proud. That I did it. That I kept going. That I created a unique destination for interesting people to find on the internet."

**The Reframe:**
> "I am not building a brand to please the algorithm. I am building a brand that allows me to talk about my writing, the writing life, games I love, and timeless truths — the big picture stuff beyond the cultural tides — while still being a full human."

