## Exercise 09 — Sustainable Foundation

### 📝 Your Answers

**Actual Weekly Hours:**
> Currently 8–10 hours/day in Athens (temporary runway). Post-July baseline: evenings and weekends around a 6–8 hour remote tech job.

**Energy Map:**
- Gives energy: Writing, streaming, writing on stream, preparing for live sessions
- Drains energy: Taking photos for thumbnails, likely video editing and social media (TBD — not yet tested)

**Realistic Cadence:**
> 2 streams per week + 1 YouTube highlight per month (delegated as soon as financially viable) + minimal personal social presence on Instagram

**Freshness Window:**
> Mornings — writing protected first, everything else after

**Preferred Creation Environment:**
> Live, in the moment. The stream is the primary creative environment.

**12–18 Month Commitment:**
> "For the next 12–18 months, I commit to streaming twice a week and shipping one YouTube highlight per month because it supports the writing and community I'm building — not because it sounds impressive."

