## Exercise 10 — Platform Strategy

### 📝 Your Answers

**Your Medium:**
> Video — live streaming as the primary creation engine, produced highlights as the distribution vehicle

**Primary Platform (discovery + growth):**
> YouTube — highlights, produced content, discovery. The front door. Eye of Sauron starts here.

**Secondary Platform (community + retention):**
> Twitch — live streams, real time engagement, paying members. The campfire.

**Warm Audience Bridge:**
> Instagram — 750 existing followers, personal presence, low effort high authenticity. Distribution channel for YouTube highlights once that system is running. Facebook exists but not a priority — wrong audience.

**Where the Eye points first and why:**
> YouTube. Discovery before retention. New people find you on YouTube, then migrate to Twitch for the live community experience. Once the highlight system is running and YouTube is dialed in, the Eye rotates to building Twitch more intentionally.

**The funnel:**
> YouTube brings people in → Twitch keeps them and builds the community → Instagram bridges warm existing audience into both

