## Exercise 11 — Ideation Table

### 📝 Your Answers

| Painful Problem | Your Unique Solution | Your Credibility |
|---|---|---|
| I'm ashamed of how deep my love for fantasy and gaming goes — I hide it from people I care about | Own it publicly and unapologetically — model what it looks like to be a serious adult who loves these things without shame | Yeezy/Skims background, serious writer, genuine gamer — never fit the stereotype and doesn't apologize for it |
| I've been working alone on something only I can see and don't know if anyone will care | Build in public — stream the work, share the process, make the invisible visible | Writing since 15, full rejection ledger, still going. The archive of streams becomes proof. |
| I'm tormented by a creative dream but too afraid to say it out loud | Say it out loud yourself, on stream, repeatedly — model the declaration | Declared it. Gone all in twice. Doing it again right now. |
| I feel like an outsider everywhere — I can't find my people | Create the destination — the channel is the camp for people who feel exactly this way | The Gentleman's Literary Forum, the Outside Inn Discord — has been building intentional communities his whole life |
| I use AI in my creative process and I'm ashamed | Talk about it openly and honestly — show exactly how you use it and why it doesn't compromise the work | Actively experimenting, building the brand with it simultaneously, sharing the process in real time |
| It feels too late — the dream won't leave me alone | Show that endurance beats timing — the long road is the only road | 10+ years of rejection, still going, myths nearly done. The ledger speaks for itself. |
| I went all in and it didn't work, I'm still going but barely | Be the person still standing — not despite the failure but because of it | Marathon got to Amblin and Heyday twice. Still in campaign. Didn't quit. |
| I keep getting disappointed by contemporary fantasy | Create the alternative — serious, beautiful, finished work that takes itself seriously | 7 myths, original cosmogonic mythology, finishing what Tolkien couldn't |
| The scale of what I want feels delusional | Normalize big creative ambition — talk about it without flinching | Writing original mythology for a fantasy world. The ambition is the whole point. |

